BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:p8xn0fV0MI_C3bTiBN_BM
SUMMARY:BE LOUD Breakfast
DTSTAMP:20260315T224737Z
DTSTART:20260317T150000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description Join us for the BE LOUD Breakfast\, an annual fundr
	aising event for the King County Sexual Assault Resource Center \\(KCSARC\
	\). This year&'s event is especially meaningful as 2026 marks the 50th ann
	iversary of KCSARC. For fifty years\, KCSARC has empowered survivors and c
	ommunities. This incredible milestone is a testament to you-our community.
	 You have shown up\, spoken out\, and stood with survivors every step of t
	he way. Today\, we face new and urgent challenges. But our mission remains
	 unwavering. Together\, we will keep moving forward-LOUDER than ever befor
	e. Will you BE LOUD with us? Register now at donate.kcsarc.org/BELOUD26\n\
	nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/be-loud-breakfast/18089678/
	2026-03-17T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/be-loud-breakfast/1808967
	8/2026-03-17T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:BjumE7rRqbfVLkxq_NESY
SUMMARY:Coworking Tuesdays
DTSTAMP:20260315T224737Z
DTSTART:20260317T163000Z
DESCRIPTION:Tuesday Cowork \\+ Coffee/Tea \\(Weekly\\) \n\nNeed a reason to
	 get out of your inbox cave and into a productive\, low-pressure space? Jo
	in us every Tuesday for a drop-in coworking morning—bring your laptop\, kn
	ock out your priorities\, and enjoy the energy of working alongside other 
	local professionals. \n\nWhen: Tuesdays | 9:30–11:30 AM | No registration 
	needed\n\nFormat: Come for the full two hours or pop in when you can\n\nWh
	o it’s for: Business owners\, remote workers\, creatives\, students\, nonp
	rofit leaders—anyone who wants focused work time \\+ light community\n\nWh
	at to expect: Quiet “get-it-done” work blocks\, optional hellos \\+ quick 
	intros\, and a friendly vibe \\(no forced networking\\) \n\nLocation \\(th
	rough February\\): Bothell Visitor Center\n\nWe’ll rotate locations monthl
	y—same time\, same Tuesday rhythm\, fresh spaces. \n\nBring: Your laptop \
	\+ whatever you need to work. We have the coffee\, tea\, and water!\n\nQue
	stions? Email sandra@bothellkenmorechamber.org\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity
	.com/events/#/details/coworking-tuesdays/17806278/2026-03-17T00\n\nFrom SE
	Atoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/coworking-tuesdays/178062
	78/2026-03-17T00
LOCATION:Bothell Kenmore Chamber\, 10031 Main Street\, Suite A\, Bothell\, 
	WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fSCWs_JgMZ1up0EjEZNJT
SUMMARY:March Madness Watch Party at Five Iron Golf - Seattle Capitol Hill
DTSTAMP:20260315T224737Z
DTSTART:20260317T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Five Iron Golf is your College Basketball HQ this March! Gather
	 your crew and book 1–2 simulator bays for up to 12 people \\(6 people per
	 bay\\) for a bracket-busting watch party experience. Enjoy all-day TV cov
	erage of college basketball alongside cutting-edge golf and multisport sim
	ulators\, a locally-inspired menu\, and custom beverage packages.\n\nBook 
	your watch party for March 19 or 20 and you'll automatically be entered to
	 win a 20-person happy hour with drinks and appetizers — a $1\,000 value!\
	n\nGroup packages can include reserved event space\, team-specific décor\,
	 a dedicated staff member\, full-screen and/or picture-in-picture viewing\
	, a customizable menu\, beverage packages\, free club rentals\, multisport
	 simulators\, and table games. Select the "Small Event" option at booking 
	to ensure simulator bays are placed side-by-side. Availability of select f
	eatures varies by location.\n\nPromotions:\n\nHappy Hour – "It's 5i o'Cloc
	k Somewhere" \\(Monday–Friday\, 3–6 PM\\)\n\nEnjoy $5 bottomless boneless 
	wings\, $10 bottomless bone-in wings\, $5 select beers/cans/cocktails\, $5
	 dips \\(guacamole\, hot honey ricotta\, hummus\\)\, half-off pizzas\, and
	 $5 featured shots. Dine-in only at participating locations\; simulator re
	ntal may be required.\n\n5i After Dark – "Swing In\, For Less"  \\(Sunday–
	Thursday 9 PM to close | Friday–Saturday 10 PM to close\\)\n\nFeatures $29
	/hr simulator rentals plus the same great food and drink specials as Happy
	 Hour\, with wings priced per dozen rather than bottomless. Dine-in only a
	t participating locations\; simulator rental may be required.\n\nhttps://s
	eatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/march-madness-watch-party-at-five-iro
	n-golf-seattle-capitol-hill/18268907/2026-03-17T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Food
	 & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/march-madness-watch-party
	-at-five-iron-golf-seattle-capitol-hill/18268907/2026-03-17T00
LOCATION:Five Iron Golf - Seattle Capitol Hill\, 1525 11th Ave Suite 100\, 
	Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT12H
END:VEVENT
